==Finnish==
([[Wiktionary:Finnish_index_y|index Y]])
===Etymology===
A compound of yh- and -deksän. The former comes from [[yksi]], while the latter is from an Iranian language, compare Kurdish [[deh]]. So the compound originally meant one (from) ten.
===Cardinal Number===
'''yhdeksän'''

#[[nine]]

